*vī'rəs, /ˈvaɪrəs/, /<tt>"vaIr@s</tt>/

===Noun===
'''virus''' ([[viruses]])

#A core of [[DNA]] or [[RNA]] surrounded by a [[protein]] coat that requires a living cell to reproduce &mdash; often causes disease in the host organism.
#A [[computer virus]].

====Usage note====
The standard plural is ''viruses''. A new plural, ''virii'' has emerged for use in the computing sense. ''viruses'' is still the preferred plural.

